data.description: This Traditional home is situated on 1.95 acres on a quiet street with beautiful views. The home offers a cozy family room with hardwood floors and wood burning fireplace with privacy doors that open into the dining room. Dining room features French doors that exit onto the back deck. Kitchen has stainless steel appliances with lots of storage space and plenty of room for a kitchen island or table. Down the hall is a full bath and staircase that leads to the 4 upstairs bedrooms, full bath, and 300 squ ft. finished bonus room on the third floor. This home also features a 2 car garage.Located 10 minutes from US 27, gas stations, Lake Herrington and 30 minutes to Lexington. Check it out!~What the seller loves about the home ''there is space for a garden, 4 wheelers, tents, a fenced paddock, and run-in shed for livestock. You will enjoy the fire pit a deck for outdoor grilling or sunbathing furthermore there is room for a pool.'' Seller loves the country setting but likes the city water, new chimney liner, and wood burning insert, smart garage door, new mailbox, New HVAC and high speed fiber internet
